Here is how you could solve this problem in Java:

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int height = 10; // replace with your actual height value
        int width = 20; // replace with your actual width value

        int temp = 2 * (height + width);
        System.out.println(temp);

        temp = height * width;
        System.out.println(temp);
    }
}
```

This program first declares two integer variables, `height` and `width`, and assigns them values. Then it calculates the product of their sum multiplied by 2 (`temp = 2 * (height + width)`), prints this value to the console, then calculates the product of `height` and `width` (`temp = height * width`) and prints this value to the console.
